wks can i buy a nursing bra everyone keeps saying i'll go up a size when my milk comes in but i havent even gone up a whole size my whole pregnancy started a small b now a full b i need to pack my hospital bag what size nursing bra for the hospital you'll need a size about what you're wearing now when your milk comes in however you really will need a bigger bra preferably without padding in spandex cups medela sells some blissfully comfortable nursing bras that i thought were a lifesaver after my other nursing bras you should also avoid nursing bras with underwires because the pressure they put on your breast even if you don't feel it can clog your milk ducts and cause infection happened to me i switched to the medela bras and haven't had a problem since sleeping nursing bras are really comfortable for the hospital for sleeping and in general they're usually pretty simple cotton pull over bras that pull down over your breast to feed you'll also want to bring a few nursing pads with you to the hospital just in case good luck and happy birth wishes to you Brassiere Breastfeeding Breast Caprice Bourret Mattress Urinary incontinence Milk Undergarment Childbirth Premature birth Dialysis Dairy Infant Mastitis Fecal incontinence Abortion Coffee Professional wrestling match types Mammary gland Marilyn Monroe Humphrey Bogart History of corsets Prolactinoma Sanitary towel 2005 trial of Michael Jackson Menstrual cup Tampon Oral contraceptive Rais massacre Diving suit Menstrual cycle Bong Vernon Schillinger Knots Landing Cytomegalovirus History of As the World Turns (2000-present) Certified Nursing Assistant RuneScape quests Vegeta Shoe Nipple piercing First aid kit Customs and etiquette of Japan Shaggy dog story Lauren Bacall Germaine Greer Nipple Genericized trademark Mojave people Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Vegetarianism Guinea pig Passenger car Melanie Wilkes Glossary of ballet terms Bicycle brake systems Traumatic brain injury Milton H. Erickson Juliana 